sequenceDiagram
  actor User
  participant Telegram
  participant API
  participant Interpreter
  participant DB
  User->>Telegram: Send finance message or question
  Telegram->>Telegram: Require linked or registered sender
  Telegram->>API: POST /webhooks/telegram
  API->>DB: Reserve provider message id
  alt message id already processed
    API-->>Telegram: 200 OK without duplicate expense
  else new message id
  API->>DB: Find user by phone number
  alt sender is not registered
    API->>DB: Mark audit as unknown_user
    API-->>Telegram: 200 OK without processing
  else registered sender
    API->>DB: Check active pending draft
    alt pending draft exists
      API->>Interpreter: Interpret reply
      API->>API: Merge reply into draft, confirm duplicate, or cancel draft
    else no pending draft
      API->>DB: Check same sender/channel/text saved in last 2 minutes
      alt possible recent duplicate
        API->>DB: Mark audit as needs_confirmation
        API->>DB: Upsert duplicate confirmation draft
        API->>Telegram: Ask user to guardar or descartar
      else not duplicate
        API->>Interpreter: Interpret intent and structured fields
        Interpreter-->>API: Amount, concept, intent, category hint, payment method; currency comes from user settings
      end
    end
    alt missing data
      API->>DB: Mark audit as needs_confirmation
      API->>DB: Upsert pending draft for user
      API->>Telegram: Ask for clarification
    else category unclear, ambiguous, or missing
      API->>DB: Mark audit as needs_confirmation
      API->>DB: Upsert category clarification draft
      API->>Telegram: Ask for exact category or subcategory
      alt duplicate subcategory name
        User->>Telegram: Reply "Dance"
        API->>Telegram: Ask to choose exact path (Education > Dance / Entertainment > Dance)
      else category does not exist
        User->>Telegram: Reply with non-existing category name
        API->>Telegram: Ask whether to create it and whether it is root or child category
        API->>DB: Create tenant-scoped category or subcategory when confirmed
      end
    else update referenced movement
      API->>DB: Read recent tenant-scoped expenses/incomes
      API->>API: Match by referenced amount, concept, category, and movement type
      API->>DB: Update amount, concept, or category when match is confident
      API->>DB: Mark audit as saved
      API->>Telegram: Confirm updated movement
    else create expense
      API->>DB: Insert expense scoped by tenant using preferred currency
      API->>DB: Mark audit as saved
      API->>Telegram: Confirm saved expense
    else create income
      API->>DB: Insert income scoped by tenant using preferred currency
      API->>DB: Mark audit as saved
      API->>Telegram: Confirm saved income
    else ask report or budget status
      API->>DB: Read tenant-scoped report or budget data
      API->>DB: Mark audit as saved
      API->>Telegram: Reply with calculated answer
    end
  end
  end
